  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan: Transferring Professional Development Capacity (TPDC)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To enable the Professional Training Departments (PTDs) of the Attorney General&apos;s Office (AGO), Ministry of Justice (MOJ), and Supreme Court (SC) to independently conduct needs assessments, develop effective curricula, deliver quality training of trainers (TOT), and monitor their training impact. 2) To ensure that the PTDs meet the extraordinary demand for Penal Code training caused by the 2017 revision. 3) To ensure that the PTDs have long-term departmental strategies and are able to manage their human resource, procurement, and budgeting needs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Personnel of the Attorney General&apos;s Office, Ministry of Justice and Supreme Court.
Indirect beneficiaries: Afghan citizens seeking justice sector-related services.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to ensure that Afghan criminal justice institutions are effective and able to uphold the rights of Afghans, because their professional staff continuously develop their capacity.</narrative>
  </description>
